	</form>
</h1>

<form action="/create" enctype="multipart/form-data" method="post">
	<table>
	<tr><th>Top left</th><th>Top centre</th><th>Top right</th></tr>
	<tr><td><input class="changeable left" id="stamp_tl" name="stamp[tl]" size="30" type="text" value="<%= @stamp.tl %>" /></td><td><input class="changeable" id="stamp_tc" name="stamp[tc]" size="30" type="text" value="<%= @stamp.tc %>" /></td><td><input class="changeable right" id="stamp_tr" name="stamp[tr]" size="30" type="text"  value="<%= @stamp.tr %>" /></td></tr>
	<tr><td colspan="3" class="pdf_loader" id="pdf_container">
		<div>
			<div>
				<input type="button" id="pdf_navig_back" value="<<"/>
				<img alt="" height="1" src="/images/nowt.gif?1314831439" width="230" />
				<input type="button" id="pdf_navig_next" value=">>"/>
			</div>
			<div id="pdf_lens_wrapper">
				<div id="pdf_lens">
					<img id="pdf_image" class="pdf_image" alt=""/>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</td></tr>
	<tr><td colspan="3" class="pdf_loader" id="pdf_form_frame">
		<iframe id="pdf_frame" src="/thumbs" frameBorder="0"></iframe>
	</td></tr>
	<tr><td><input class="changeable left" id="stamp_bl" name="stamp[bl]" size="30" type="text" value="<%= @stamp.bl %>" /></td><td><input class="changeable" id="stamp_bc" name="stamp[bc]" size="30" type="text" value="<%= @stamp.bc %>" /></td><td><input class="changeable right" id="stamp_br" name="stamp[br]" size="30" type="text" value="<%= @stamp.br %>" /></td></tr>
	<tr><th>Bottom left</th><th>Bottom centre</th><th>Bottom right</th></tr>
	</table>

  <p>
    <b>Start page numbering at:</b> <input class="changeable" id="stamp_start_page" name="stamp[start_page]" size="30" type="text" value="<%= @stamp.start_page %>" />
  </p>

	<input id="stamp_timezone" name="stamp[timezone]" type="hidden" value="<%= @stamp.timezone %>" />
	<input id="stamp_filename" name="stamp[filename]" type="hidden" value="<%= @stamp.filename %>" />

  <p>
    <input name="commit" type="submit" value="Create" />

    	<input name="commit" type="submit" value="Show data" />

  </p>
</form>

<p>
Put text to be stamped over your Celtx-generated pdf in the six positional boxes above. Choose the pdf itself in the central box. Text will be stamped in the appropriate positions on your pdf, in 10pt Courier.
</p>
<p>
Click on the image of the page to upload a new script.
</p>
<p>
The following macros can be used:
<table>
	<tr><td><b>%Page%</b></td><td>The current page number</td></tr>
	<tr><td><b>%Pages%</b></td><td>The total number of pages in the numbered page section</td></tr>
	<tr><td><b>%Date%</b></td><td>The current date</td></tr>
	<tr><td><b>%Time%</b></td><td>The current time</td></tr>
</table>
</p>
<p>
The start page number defaults to 0. Only pages with page numbers of 1 or greater will be stamped, so if you have a title page on your pdf, starting at 0 will mean stamping doesn't start until the first actual page of script. If you have no title page, change this to 1 and stamping will begin right at the beginning; if your script's page 1 is on the fourth page of the pdf, then the first page of the pdf is effectively page -2, so stick that in the box. Note that existing Celtx-created page numbers will be deleted. Complex? Not a bit of it.
</p>
<p>
Please note that this system has only been tested against pdfs generated by Celtx, and is not guaranteed in any way at all. But it'll hopefully work, and not cause global warming.
</p>
